Grammy&#039;s Greatest Moments, Vol. 4 Review

07/13/2005 5:42 AM, AMG

Grammy&#039;s Greatest Moments, Vol. 4 continues the series of live performances taken from the yearly awards telecast, with most of the selections on this volume dating from the early &#039;80s and early &#039;90s. It may be disconcerting to some to have Rick Springfield, Irene Cara, Herbie Hancock, and Sheena Easton performing their early-&#039;80s hits next to Amy Grant, Melissa Etheridge, Seal, and Sting, but overall, the music isn&#039;t all that dissimilar, making it a worthy entry in the series. ~ Steve Huey, All Music Guide
